  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A personal injury damage suit\nwas filed in the superior court by\nNels Anderson this morning\nagainst the Great Northern Rail-\nroad Co. While riding over the\nroad from Newport to Elk, Wash,\nlast fall Nels was violently thrown\nfrom his seat and came in contact\nwith about everything there was in\nthe car before he could stop, as the\nresult of the train leaving the\ntracks. When Nels was able to\ntake an inventory of himself he\nfound he had sustained injuries\nabout the face, neck and shoulders\nwhich he appraises at $4,000."
    }
  ]
